    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Breve de terra de Franciano. Ut facta hominum et dicta bene et ordinatim ad
                        memoriam possint reduci bonum est et equum, quod placuit et convenit
                        litteris planis comprehendere sive excipere. Divina enim potentia, sive
                        sponsa Christi ecclesia, redeuntibus vel peccatoribus aut penitentibus
                        nunquam gremio claudit vel contradicit suum, et quia carnale est peccare,
                        divinum est peccatum extinguere. Huius rei causa <rs key="#Countess"
                            >comitissa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Countess" ref="#people/101">Adalascia</persName>, coniux
                            <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/97">Raineri</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs>, precibusque porrectis <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbati</rs>
                        <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/108">Cunizo</persName> simulque cum
                        suis <rs key="#Monks">fratribus</rs> quod iniuste contradicebat sive
                        contendebat, scilicet <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terram</rs> de <placeName ref="#places/89"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Franciano</placeName> ad <rs key="#Monasteries">abbadia sive
                            monasterio</rs> de <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/78"
                            key="#Monasteries">Sancto Quirico sive Sancti Salvatoris</orgName>, quam
                        pluribus <rs key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">bonis hominibus </rs>adstantibus
                        sive presentibus tenore vel modo suprascripto refutavit, et animo spontaneo
                        promisit medietatem supradicte terre de Franciano nullo tempore nec ipsa,
                        nec suis heredes nec alius per eam nec tollere, nec contendere nec ullo modo
                        contradicere. Quin etiam ab omni homine se promisit defendere per rectam et
                        bonam fidem, sine malo ingenio. Hoc factum est in loco <placeName
                            ref="#places/87"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Residential #Castle #Countess #Itinerary"
                            >Suvereto</placeName> infra ipsum <rs key="#Castle">castellum</rs>. Anno
                        ab incarnatione domini millesimo nonagesimo sexto, VI nonas iulii. <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Sicherius">Sicherius</name></persName> filius
                                <persName><name ref="Ildebrandus">Ildibrandi</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Guilielmus"
                            >Wilielmus</name></persName> filius <persName><name ref="Hugolinus"
                                >Ugolini</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Hugo">Ugo</name></persName> filius <persName><name
                                ref="Paganus">Pagani</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Albertus">Alberto</name></persName> filius
                                <persName><name ref="Baroncellus">Baroncelli</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Teutius/Modanensis">Teuzo
                                Modanensis</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Suavitius">Suavizo</name></persName> filius <persName><name
                                ref="Rusticus">Rustici</name></persName>, hii omnes et plures alii
                        testes huius rei rogati sunt. </ab>
                </div>
